{"parse":{"title":"Michael Williams (geographer)","pageid":54670232,"revid":816646428,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Michael Williams</b> (1935\u20132009) was a Welsh historical geographer, known particularly for his work on <a href=\"/wiki/Deforestation\" title=\"Deforestation\">deforestation</a>. He had a personal chair at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\">University of Oxford</a> from 1996.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODNB_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODNB-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Michael_Williams_(geographer)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He was the second son of Benjamin Williams and his wife, Ethel Mary Marshell of <a href=\"/wiki/Swansea\" title=\"Swansea\">Swansea</a>, born in Rheanfa House Maternity Hospital. He studied at <a href=\"/wiki/University_College,_Swansea\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University College, Swansea\">University College, Swansea</a> from 1953, and fell under the influence of the geographer <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Frank_Emery&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Frank Emery (page does not exist)\">Frank Emery</a>. He graduated B.A.\nin 1956, and Ph.D. in 1960 with a thesis on the <a href=\"/wiki/Somerset_Levels\" title=\"Somerset Levels\">Somerset Levels</a>. By that time married, he moved on to <a href=\"/wiki/St_Catharine%27s_College,_Cambridge\" title=\"St Catharine&#39;s College, Cambridge\">St Catharine's College, Cambridge</a>, working for an education diploma.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODNB_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODNB-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later in 1960, Williams took a lecturing post at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Adelaide\" title=\"University of Adelaide\">University of Adelaide</a>, becoming reader in 1970. In 1978 he went to the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\">University of Oxford</a>, where he was a reader from 1990, professor from 1996, and a Fellow of <a href=\"/wiki/Oriel_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oriel College\">Oriel College</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODNB_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODNB-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He was elected a fellow of the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Academy\" title=\"British Academy\">British Academy</a> in 1989.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Professor emeritus from 2002, Williams died of <a href=\"/wiki/Adult_respiratory_distress_syndrome\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Adult respiratory distress syndrome\">adult respiratory distress syndrome</a> on 26 October 2009.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODNB_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODNB-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Michael_Williams_(geographer)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Williams's books included:<sup id=\"cite_ref-ODNB_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ODNB-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li><i>The Draining of the Somerset Levels</i> (1970)</li>\n<li><i>The Making of the South Australian Landscape</i> (1976)</li>\n<li><i>The Changing Rural Landscape of South Australia</i> (1977)</li>\n<li><i>Americans and their Forests</i> (1989), Charles A. Weyerhaeuser Book Award of the American Forest and Conservation Society</li>\n<li><i>Deforesting the Earth, from Prehistory to Global Crisis</i> (2003), Weyerhaeuser Book Award and Meridian Prize of the Association of American Geographers.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Michael_Williams_(geographer)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ODNB-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODNB_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODNB_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODNB_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODNB_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ODNB_1-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFClout\" class=\"citation encyclopaedia\">Clout, Hugh. \"Williams, Michael\". <i><a href=\"/wiki/Dictionary_of_National_Biography#Oxford_Dictionary_of_National_Biography\" title=\"Dictionary of National Biography\">Oxford Dictionary of National Biography</a></i> (online ed.). Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1093/ref%3Aodnb/103455\">10.1093/ref:odnb/103455</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Williams%2C+Michael&amp;rft.btitle=Oxford+Dictionary+of+National+Biography&amp;rft.edition=online&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1093%2Fref%3Aodnb%2F103455&amp;rft.aulast=Clout&amp;rft.aufirst=Hugh&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMichael+Williams+%28geographer%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> <span style=\"font-size:0.95em; font-size:90%; color:#555\">(Subscription or <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external tex